gomodel:SYNGO_1129  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: KA1 (kainate) receptor.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has ligand-gated ion channel receptor activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (shown with high-resolution technique). The inference to term ligand-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099507) is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[Q8BMF5] SyNGO ID 1120 (PMID:12954862, EM). Experimental description: For these experiments, the GluK4 plasmid from the Heinemann laboratory was subcloned into the pCIneo vector (Promega Corporation, Madison, WI, USA) for use in mammalian cells.\n\n29/6/2018 Pim\n- I have selected 'human' as the species of the expressed protein. The leader of the lab that contributed the cDNA (Heinemann SF) passed away several years ago." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1129" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
